The most illogical argument I can think of

Trying to come up with logical arguments to disprove the existence of God is
very frustrating because if God truly exists and is all-powerful then logic
itself is dictated by God. This means that God can shape reality in such a way
that any true or false logical statement can become the opposite or that the
system of logic itself can be redefined to make any given argument false or
true. Of course, under conventional logic, this does not prove the existence of
God, but it sure does give one something to think about.
